children.subject: The lab you have selected conflicts with another course you are already enrolled in and so campus systems will not move you into the class. Perhaps the other new lab section does not conflict with an already enrolled class or perhaps you wish to prioritize taking 61BL over 70 and can drop 70.  Taking 70 and 61BL together in the shortened summer session is not recommended.
what are my chances of getting of the CS70 waitlist if I am 37th on the waitlist?

Which are the new sections that have been added to 61C?

history.content:
New:  COMPSCI C8 is now on the schedule of classes for Summer 17.  (It is also listed as STAT & INFO C8 but all enrollments for SU 17 will be funneled through the CS listing).  People can enroll now.  It is now projected to have an enrollment limit of 60 but if demand warrants it can probably be expanded to ~ 90.

Expanded: Both 61BL & 61C had two new sections added and their lecture capacities increased.  Students on the waitlists were emailed and encouraged to drop and re-waitlist for the new sections.  New students who are interested can also add themselves to the waitlist and I think that automatic waitlist processing for summer session classes is occurring and students who are waitlisted for sections with capacity should be moved into those classes tomorrow morning.
